<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="300" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1499.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-07-31"><hi rend="italic">
                                        July</hi> 31, 1865</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 13th instant,
                            informing me of your intention to endeavor to obtain further evidence in
                            regard to the armament of the Stonewall, <hi rend="italic">alias</hi>
                            the Olinde, has been received and is approved.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c. London.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>